title: Success is not how high you climbed but how you made a positive difference
I'm thankful to have been Blessed with another day!  How about you; what are you thankful for?

My journey to the healthiest I can be.  It's been quite the adventure.  I've come a long way and it's not over! Always room for progress! On January 9,2017 I had a total abdominal hysterectomy with bilateral salpingo oophorectomy. 30 staples over the stit
Closest thing I've made to a wreath this year... hair braids while watching this movie.... really need a load outta here, gotta go catch the monies! 💰
My cat Abby on the hood of one of Dads old dump trucks.  Thought I had a picture of that truck somewhere, guess it's in another album.
Me in 1985 playing with critters at home
1985; first grade.. Durant Iowa bowling alley, first place trophies that year.
That time I moved the firewood out of the wood box to build myself a fort... about nine years old.
Captain Casey isn't sure why we put this shiny light up imitation tree in his house.  🌲 🌲 🎄 🎄
Captain Casey waiting for us to find a load for the Freightliner...or maybe a bowl of kibble is what he's really after.
Captain Casey watching Alice through the looking glass with us. Freightliner in the driveway ready to go soon as find a decent load.
All the room in here and Onyx still has to get as close as possible... big teddy bear anyway these days...

ButterBean says he wants a corvette for his birthday and Christmas present... so I find this... tell him ok I'll get you one, let me borrow your card a minute need to use ten dollars... apparently this isn't what he's trying to acquire.
Captain Casey lounging around watching television...
Food we can't get from a truckstop... home cooked stuff!
Captain Casey says being home is nice and all but we need Freightliner to fix the money maker.  Hopefully tomorrow it'll be ready.
I see a face and wind blown hair.... cloud watching the many things that can appear up there and change faster than a kaleidoscope.
And the puppies are going to the animal services. He said they'll be took care of, they vet and adopt them out.

Pretty sky again tonight. Sure is nice and quiet here.  I hear crickets off in the distance. Wish my camera could capture the view as well as looking up here myself, some things just have to be done in person.
I did it again. Let's see what ButterBean does with it now....
Mom's family: Claudia, David, Mom, George, Connie, & me
I cooked some type of stuff, ButterBean called it supper and said it was good!
Hello Moon! Wherever we are, near and far... we're under the same Moon, living on the same planet...
About time to get this semi truck away from the house... looks like Mother Nature might provide a truck wash if I time this just right...
No load today so let's do something else productive! Replace the a-coil in our indoor climate system....
Hey Onyx, what ya think about the lack of freight available to us?
Captain Casey would rather be riding in it than looking at it in the driveway... with any luck dispatch will send a decent load along today.

Dinner time! We got pork chops, fish, taters, red beans and rice, corn, butter beans! And ButterBean says it's good so that's a plus, now if we can find a load for that semi truck as good as what dinner is we'll be all set. 😁 😁

Onyx and Captain Casey are still miffed about our load getting cancelled and the fact we're still home awaiting a decent load for our semi truck to show itself.   Soon guys, won't be long we'll be back on the road catching our money again!! 💰 :do
Another beautiful day! Tomorrow we take that semi to the east coast, nice to be able to enjoy a bit of time at home.
My best friend sees a scary scene in a movie and has to hold my hand...
Captain Casey seems to like my fuzzy pajamas...
Captain Casey and Onyx at home watching tv... The Transporter movie...
So I messed up my nails when I attempted to fix them...but it's all good, my little flying friend seems to like them.  💕
Peace, Safety, Security, Strength, Love, Happiness, whatever the need may be let it come to being ~ None too small nor too large, all is possible ~Blessed Be~
